		<title>17FARMING-CROSSGATES AREA</title>
		<content>                                       
 Farming is still the main land use    
 despite the growth of housing in the  
 Crossgates and Halbeath area.         
 Even the main industry in the area    
 ,the open cast mine ,is used for      
 farming over most of its area (see    
 pages on mining in Crossgates area)   
 The main crop is grass which is used  
 for direct grazing and for the making 
 of silage. Other crops include barley 
 and oilseed rape as well as potateos, 
 brussel sprouts, cabbages and turnips.
 Both beef and dairy cows are raised in
 the area.                             
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
